interactive session on cm4 inter
srun -M inter -p cm4_inter -n 1 -c 32 --cpu-bind=cores --sockets-per-node=1 --hint=nomultithread --pty bash

srun \
  -M inter \
  -p cm4_inter \
  -n 1 \
  -c 64 \                    # Allocate 64 logical cores (Higher than your 16/32 tests)
  --cpu-bind=cores \         # Binds processes to physical cores (Prevents "thread drifting" across the Mesh)
  --sockets-per-node=1 \     # Keeps all execution within a single physical CPU socket
  --hint=nomultithread \     # DISABLES Hyper-threading (Prevents the performance collapse seen at 17-24 threads)
  --pty bash                 # Opens an interactive terminal session



cm4 tiny:
srun -M cm4 -p cm4_tiny -n 1 -c 32 --hint=nomultithread --cpu-bind=cores --pty bash


get a whole node: 
srun -M inter -p cm4_inter --exclusive -N 1 --pty bash


see what threads are pinned to our task:  taskset -cp $$